Believe me, you are a failure, incapable of doing something worthless, unlovable, a joke that the living and the dead laugh at, even if they praise you, they lie to exploit you and

Don't you dare try to get these thoughts out of your head, it's the undeniable truth, and I'm going to help you preserve it for ever

Imprisoned in these thoughts, unable to advance, but able to retreat, he is pulled by negative thoughts embodied in the form of a ghost, which drag him into the depths of darkness, tied to metal chains that burn the skin! poor

Will he survive these thoughts and become the master of himself, or will he remain captive forever in the darkness, devoured by thoughts and torn to pieces?
